result.execSummary:
The defendant John Frederick Cleveland was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. John Frederick Cleveland is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • John Frederick Cleveland was found guilty of Possession of Marijuana. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant John Frederick Cleveland in court with attorney Michael L. Chernin.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  AS TO COUNT 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered count dimissed.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to POSSESSION OF THC contrary to County Ordinance 24.01 to which the defendant entered a plea guilty.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered him to pay a forfeiture of $100.00 inclusive of costs to be paid by 10-05-2015 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

Defendant John Frederick Cleveland in court with attorney Michael L. Chernin.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Defense requested a final pretrial and jury trial date in Branch 24.  Final pre-trial scheduled for August 6, 2015 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for August 31, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Michael L. Chernin in court, defendant John Frederick Cleveland not in court, in custody.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  The defendant is in federal custody.  Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered the stayed bench warrant continued to the next court date.  Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 24.  Status conference scheduled for June 3, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant John Frederick Cleveland not in court.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  No appearance by Defendant nor Attorney Cernin.  Court ordered a bench warrant but STAYED issuance until next court date.  Attempted to contact Attorney, but no return phone call as of Wednesday, May 13, 2015.  Status conference scheduled for May 18, 2015 at 08:30 am.

No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant John Frederick Cleveland in court with attorney Michael L. Chernin.  Defendant John Frederick Cleveland in custody.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Protasiewicz, Branch 24.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for May 12, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
